    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the CFD model, supported by Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and multi-laboratory experimental validation, provides sufficient evidence that predicted NIH values remain below the clinical threshold across the five COU operating points. Although multiple credibility factors show achieved levels below required levels, the conservative 95th-percentile UQ bound provides additional margin. The orphan claim regarding absolute hemolysis acceptability was reviewed in prose and deemed adequate by the team without formal evidence traceability linkage.",
